    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters April 7th with high-floor expectations, anchored by the elite daily efficiency of **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (74.83). **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and favorable platoon splits against the right-handed Burrows, making him a primary target for counting stats. Meanwhile, **Vinnie Pasquantino** thrives in a prime #3 hole matchup against Williams, whose 4.35 xERA offers plenty of runway for a high-output performance. We are also tracking **Corbin Carroll** (68.01) closely; while his matchup against Peralta is statistically daunting, his 92% stolen base success probability against this specific battery, combined with his lead-off/two-hole speed dynamic, makes him an essential start despite the SP skill penalty.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Zach McKinstry**, whose 50.73 score was hindered by a negative platoon shift despite a solid SP matchup against Bradley. He fell just short of bumping **Jose Caballero** (50.78), whose lineup spot and platoon struggles against Civale create a narrow margin of error. We are prioritizing high-OPS upside with **James Wood** (73.10) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (73.10) today; **James Wood** is particularly well-positioned at leadoff to capitalize on Liberatore\u2019s pedestrian skill profile. As we monitor the board, keep a watchful eye on the risk profile for **Gabriel Moreno** and **Josh Naylor**, both of whom are facing high-end arms in Peralta and Eovaldi, respectively. These players are currently starting, but their efficiency remains tethered to the defensive positioning and bullpen volatility inherent in early-season matchups.",
